Share this on WhatsAppBandits sustaining their onslaught, on Monday killed about 10 person in fresh operation in a community near the Government Science School, Kuru, Jos South Local Government Area, Plateau State.
The bandits were said to have struck in the early hours of Monday.
Residents of Kuru Community, Jos South Council Area, Plateau State, are still counting their losses, including mourning the 12 persons killed by bandits on Sunday night.
The bandits had invaded the Kuru Community at about 9.00p.m., killing 12 persons while  five others were said to have survived the onslaught, escaping with various degrees of injuries. They were said to be receiving treatment at certain hospitals in the state.
Details of the Monday attacks are still awaited.
